- Try to Take snapshot
    - Open history-manager
    - Install or remove a package
    - Push take snapshot button
    - Observe that after taking snapshot whether the history manager screen can be refreshed and show new changes.

- Try to push details button
    Go console and type 
    pisi hs
    Compare the last changes with history manager. 

- Try to push Show operation plan button
     Go console and type·
     $ pisi hs
     - Compare the last changes with history manager.
        Observe that the package(s) will be updated, installed or removed correctly.

- Try to push Take Changes Back button
    - Observe after taking changes back 
        - Whether the history manager screen can be refreshed.
        - Push the show operations button of time that you had taken the operation(s) back.
            - Observe that operation(s) had been removed from the show operation plan list.
     Go console and type·
     $ pisi hs
     - Compare the last changes with history manager.
        Observe that the operations that had taken back are listed correctly.

